---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import SvgComponentConverter from '../../components/SvgComponentConverter.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Free SVG to React Component Converter - JSX & TSX"
  description="Convert raw SVG markup into clean React JSX or TSX components locally in your browser. Preview the SVG and copy component code instantly."
>
  <SvgComponentConverter />

  <article class="bg-white p-8 rounded-2xl shadow-sm border border-slate-200 prose max-w-none mt-4 text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
    <h2 id="features" class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4 border-b pb-2 border-slate-100">Why Convert SVG to Components?</h2>
    <p class="mb-4 text-sm">React components make icons easier to reuse, style, and pass props into. This converter handles common SVG-to-JSX attribute changes and keeps everything local.</p>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mb-6 text-sm flex flex-col gap-2">
      <li><strong>JSX and TSX:</strong> Switch between plain React components and typed SVG props.</li>
      <li><strong>Prop Ready:</strong> Generated components spread props onto the root SVG.</li>
      <li><strong>Safer Preview:</strong> Script-like content is removed before rendering.</li>
    </ul>
    <h2 id="faq" class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4 border-b pb-2 border-slate-100">Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)</h2>
    <p class="text-sm text-slate-600">The output is designed for React projects. Vue conversion can be added later as a separate mode.</p>
  </article>
</Layout>
